<TEXT>
elmer johnson executive vice president and a 
director of general motors corp plans to leave the automaker and 
return to a chicago law firm the detroit free press reported in 
saturdays editions 
the official announcement is expected to come when gms board of 
directors meets monday according to gm executives who spoke to the 
newspaper on the condition of anonymity 
johnson 56 decided to leave his job because his 
oftencontroversial ideas to change the nations top automaker have 
been ignored the executives said 
johnson was on vacation and couldnt be reached and gm declined 
official comment the newspaper said 
dan vittum a partner in the chicago law firm of kirkland amp 
ellis wouldnt confirm that johnson was returning to the firm 
johnson has remained a partner in the firm since joining gm in 
1983 he sits on its management committee for which he receives 
30000 annually vittum said 
