<TEXT>
the polk county sheriffs office is making 
its own crack these days having decided it is a safer and more 
efficient way to supply its undercover agents for sales to drug 
buyers 
while most law enforcement agencies use crack confiscated during 
investigations for undercover operations polk officials decided 
they needed more than the very limited supply of crack they had 
on hand a department report said 
in addition there were worries about impurities sometimes found 
in confiscated crack 
turning powder cocaine into crack cocaine requires a powdery 
base substance as well as the drug some dealers have been known to 
use drano or other toxic chemicals as the base sheriffs lt james 
madden said recently 
after reviewing all our options and checking with other 
agencies in the state that are taking an aggressive approach to 
crack we felt the safest and most reliable way to handle these 
reverses would be use crack that was produced in a clean 
controlled environment the report said 
polk county deputies posing as drug dealers have routinely set 
up shop in known drug neighborhoods and sold crack to drug buyers 
in cars deputies have made more than 600 reversesting arrests 
since the campaign began in earnest last fall 
the sheriffs office crack was made at the department by a 
supervisor in the drug unit who had gone over the fairly simple 
cooking procedure with technicians from the florida department of 
law enforcement baking powder was used as a base substance 
the cooking session produced 11 ounces enough to make several 
thousand pieces of crack in the size commonly sold on the street 
officials said 
</TEXT>
