floods and landslides caused by more than a week 
of heavy rains have killed 62 people in two provinces in eastern 
china official reports said today 
six of the victims were children killed when a waterlogged 
school building collapsed in zhejiang provinces longquan county 
the official china daily reported 
heavy rains also fell this week in jiangxi province on 
zhejiangs western border causing a landslide that killed at least 
17 people the paper said 
reports today did not specify where or how the other 39 people 
died 
the xinhua news agency said 212420 acres of farmland have been 
flooded and nearly 6400 homes destroyed in zhejiang since the 
rains began june 15 
the rains in jiangxi have flooded 568000 acres of farmland and 
forced 14000 people to flee their homes the china daily said 
the report said four to 12 inches of rain fell on various parts 
of zhejiang during a 10day period ending friday zhejiang normally 
receives about four inches of rain during the entire month of june 
in china the rainy season generally lasts until midjuly and 
more storms are forecast 
heavy storms last month in the same area of china killed at 
least 131 people and heavily damaged crops 
