the trustees of atlanta university and clark 
college voted friday to merge the schools into a new entity clark 
atlanta university 
atlanta university is the financially troubled graduate school 
of the atlanta university center a consortium of clark morehouse 
college morris brown college and spelman college the morehouse 
school of medicine and the interdenominational theological center 
the merger of clark an undergraduate school with the graduate 
school alters a nearly 60yearold agreement among the seven 
historically black colleges to jointly finance maintenance 
management and some academic programs 
the new school will become the largest member of the consortium 
in terms of students and budget with its annual budget placed at 
30 million and 2000 undergraduates and 1000 graduate students 
clark president thomas w cole jr will be chief executive 
officer of the new institution 
