<TEXT>
two years of turmoil has taken a physical 
toll of arizonas lawmakers who had to deal with the governors 
timeconsuming impeachment trial and face raising taxes 200 
million just months before reelection bids 
their current session set a record friday as the longest in 
state history and theyre far from finished with their business 
i dont think theres a member here whos not among the 
walking wounded said house minority leader art hamilton a 
phoenix democrat 
im just exhausted said senate majority leader bob usdane 
a republican from scottsdale 
it doesnt feel good said house speaker joe lane 
friday was the 166th day of the session but taxes budgets and 
about 50 other pieces of legislation are still not settled and the 
lawmakers are operating on reduced pay increased fatigue and in 
some cases worse health 
in theory legislative sessions are supposed to end by the 
saturday of the week in which the 100th day falls 
but the house impeachment and senate trial of gov evan mecham 
took weeks out of each chambers schedule this year and the trauma 
started last year when mecham faced off against a largely 
inexperienced set of legislative leaders 
the stage was set in 1986 when thengov bruce babbitt decided 
to run for president house majority leader burton barr decided to 
run for governor speaker james sossaman ran for senate and senate 
president stan turley and minority leader alfredo gutierrez retired 
mecham beat barr in a rough republican primary election and 
clashed repeatedly with the republicancontrolled legislature 
until this year when the senate ousted him on april 4 
now mecham loyalists are vowing revenge at the polls and 
democrats are drooling at the prospect of increased numbers in both 
chambers 
many republican incumbents simply arent running for 
reelection and others such as lane face uphill election fights 
if they find the time to gather signatures on their nominating 
petitions before the june 30 deadline 
among the casualties 
hal runyan the senates majority whip suffered a stroke 
while undergoing an operation and is confined to a wheelchair he 
comes in only for key votes and will not seek reelection 
greg lunn touted as one of the gops rising young stars 
aggravated a preulcerous condition and has decided to run for 
county supervisor instead of reelection 
jim ratliff the house majority leader suffered a heart 
attack and is retiring 
sterling ridge a glendale republican also is retiring 
citing health reasons 
hamilton in his 16th year as a representative said it was a 
very stressful session it is the cumulative effect of the mecham 
administration and the kind of meanness that was there all of 
this madness 
hamilton and senate democratic leader alan stephens say 
republican leaders bear some of the blame for allowing the session 
to continue drifting along 
weve been putting things off and putting things off and 
putting things off said stephens who estimated that 75 bills 
were languishing without debate while lawmakers cool their heels 
to paraphrase winston churchill never have so many worked 
for so long for so little hamilton said thursday after senate 
finance committee chairman jeff hill staged his second walkout of 
the week spiking a tentative tax agreement 
other than mechams impeachment lawmakers faced three major 
issues this year air quality indigent health care and a state 
budget of about 3 billion 
an airquality bill is on the governors desk but theres no 
agreement on indigent health or budgets 
lawmakers draw salaries of 15000 a year and extended their 
regular expense pay for 30 days beyond the normal 120day limit 
but since then they have been operating on reduced pay of 10 a day 
for phoenixarea lawmakers and 20 a day for those from outside 
maricopa county 
some grouchiness is a standard feature at every endofsession 
crunch as lawmakers confront issues they avoided at first but 
between the mecham trials unheeled scars and the prospect of 
election fights ahead lawmakers lobbyists and others say things 
seem worse than usual 
it just isnt as much fun said lunn 
the previous record 165 days was set in 1976 
