a shoving match with the crowd of democratic union supporters and 
onlookers 
a rally staged by another group the national front was then 
allowed to go ahead apparently because they back official policies 
and are not challenging the monopoly of the communist party 
police tried to break up the demonstrations by throwing up a 
cordon dividing them shouting at citizens to move along and 
waiting for the rest to disperse gradually 
mityunov said earlier the democratic union which was set up in 
may held a sanctioned meeting for about four hours with 1000 
participants in leningrad friday 
