<TEXT>
a us company has designed a 
wristwatch that alerts moslems when its time to pray and even 
shows them the direction of the holy city of mecca from 120 cities 
around the world a newspaper said saturday 
an alarm sounds 10 minutes before each days five prayer 
periods the englishlanguage saudi gazette said 
the actual time is dictated by the position of the sun 
according to the koran islams holy book which also decrees that 
the faithful should face mecca while praying 
traditionally the five daily prayer calls are made by muezzins 
or priests who summon the faithful from minarets attached to 
mosques 
nowadays prayer periods are published by newspapers and 
broadcast by radio and television stations in moslem countries 
the watch has been developed by sysorex international a 
computer systems company based in mountain view calif the 
newspaper said 
the gazette quoted abdullah saadan the sysorex agent in the 
middle east as saying the watch communicates in both arabic and 
english and gives both gregorian and hijra or islamic calendar 
dates 
to overcome differences between moslem scholars over how prayer 
times should be determined saadan said the times programmed into 
the watch have been approved by several islamic bodies 
the watch comes in various models ranging in price from 85 to 
115 the newspaper said 
</TEXT>
