a puerto rican separatist wanted in the 
united states has been granted political asylum in mexico and 
paroled after serving five years of an eightyear murder sentence 
news reports said saturday 
william morales 37 was released from prison at 9 am friday 
but authorities did not confirm it until late afternoon the 
reports in the leftist newspapers la jornada and uno mas uno said 
the united states wanted him extradited to serve out a prison 
sentence on weapons and explosives charges but mexico decided this 
month that his was a political case not covered by the extradition 
treaty between the two countries 
us officials say morales is a bomb maker for the puerto rican 
separatist group armed forces of national liberation or faln he 
was convicted in 1979 after an explosion at a clandestine bomb 
factory new york the explosion shattered his arms and left him 
badly disfigured 
morales escaped from the prison ward of bellevue hospital in new 
york a month after he was sentenced to a 29 to 89year prison term 
on on state charges and up to 10 years on federal charges 
he made his way to mexico where he was taken into custody in 
1983 he was sentenced for his role in the death of one policeman 
and the wounding of another on may 26 1983 near the central city 
of puebla and for entering mexico illegally 
la jornada which has been following morales case closely 
reported that federal interior department immigration agents took 
charge of the prisoner after his release 
all government offices were closed saturday and it was not 
possible to learn morales whereabouts 
the competing uno mas uno newspaper quoted a city government 
statement as saying that the parole was granted after 5 years and 
27 days in agreement with policies that allow release for 
prisoners who have served twothirds of their sentence 
la jornadas original report on the mexican government decision 
quoted a resolution signed by foreign minister bernardo sepulveda 
as saying that morales was granted asylum on grounds he was a 
political fighter 
it said the resolution concludes that morales did not arrive 
at producing harm to society or any individuals in particular 
except those he inflicted upon himself 
a foreign ministry spokesman confirmed the report on the 
resolution 
