four arabs stabbed and wounded an israeli 
reserve soldier near tel aviv on saturday and a bomb exploded near 
an israeli passenger bus as it drove through the occupied west 
bank the military said 
no one on the bus was hurt but the vehicle was damaged and 
jewish settlers threatened to retaliate 
earlier saturday troops shot and wounded a palestinian in the 
west bank 
the army said the soldier was attacked after the arabs tried to 
wrest away his weapon as he was hitchhiking near tel aviv at the 
major mesubim junction it said he was slightly wounded and was 
taken to tel hashomer hospital 
the national news agency itim said the soldier chaim yosef 38 
managed to reach a police station after being stabbed and told 
police of the attack 
itim quoted yosef as saying the arabs stopped their car got out 
and demanded his weapon when he refused they stabbed him and sped 
away itim said 
it said police put up roadblocks and detained suspects 
in the west bank the driver of an israeli bus headed toward the 
cooperative settlement of homesh heard a loud explosion and an 
initial investigation showed it was either a roadside bomb or an 
explosive device thrown at the bus the army said 
the army spokesman who spoke on condition of anonymity didnt 
know how many people were in the bus at the time 
israel television quoted residents of homesh 37 miles north of 
jerusalem as saying they planned to block the road linking the 
west bank towns of jenin and nablus and hold a demonstration 
protesting attacks on israeli vehicles 
on friday a homesh man and his wife were slightly injured when 
moslem worshipers stoned their car in nablus the man opened fire 
with an uzi submachine gun and wounded seven arabs including two 
8yearold boys 
a top aide to prime minister yitzhak shamir said israel could 
not see the light at the end of the tunnel and predicted the 
arab uprising against israeli occupation of the west bank and the 
gaza strip would continue over an extended period 
a palestinian was slightly wounded in the leg in the west bank 
town of nablus when soldiers opened fire to disperse protesters in 
the citys casbah or arab bazaar the army said 
officials at nablus al ittihad hospital identified him as 
20yearold nahel mohammed elarbudi and said four other arabs were 
treated for tear gas inhalation 
in arab east jerusalem police detained 10 arabs after scattered 
stonethrowing incidents israel radio reported 
police in riot gear patrolled the streets and stood guard at the 
entrances to the walled old city 
police also were seen stopping arab vehicles and checking 
papers police closed some streets to traffic 
in one incident youths hurled stones and bottles at a police 
van from a schoolyard but there were no injuries police searched 
the school letting out the students one by one 
police closed three arab private schools according to jerusalem 
police spokesman rafi levy he said the closures followed 
stonethrowing attacks 
police have linked the renewed tension in jerusalem to the 
latest leaflet put out by palestinian leaders it called on the 
arabs to intensify protests in jerusalem and challenge israeli rule 
over the city 
the leaflet designated sunday as a day of attacks on arabs 
working for israels military administration in the occupied lands 
in gaza city israeli troops demolished the second floor of a 
house welded shut the doors of eight stores and sealed three side 
streets in retaliation for a firebomb attack monday that injured 
two soldiers the army said 
in the west bank town of ramallah a protest erupted in the 
central manara square after about 200 moslem fundamentalists met at 
the nearby mosque israeli witnesses said they said troops fired 
tear gas and rubber bullets to disperse protesters no injuries 
were reported 
also saturday a fire broke out in a forest on the slopes of mt 
tabor in northern israel and about 5000 trees were destroyed 
itim reported israel radio quoted police as saying it was arson 
israeli officials have blamed palestinian nationalists for more 
than 100 cases of arson since january 
