<TEXT>
friends and literary contemporaries of jack 
kerouac reunited saturday to remember the man who defined the 
beat generation of the 1950s 
a replay of kerouacs reading of the final paragraph of his 
classic novel on the road from a 1959 television show 
culminated the dedication of a oneacre park commemorating the 
lowellborn author 
the 90minute ceremony attended by about 1000 people including 
two of kerouacs three wives and poets allen ginsberg and lawrence 
ferlinghetti officially opened the first public memorial to 
kerouac in lowell and sought to settle past controversy over the 
project 
ultimately the quality of the work overshadows all the other 
issues said lowell mayor richard howe one of the fundamental 
principals of the park is to encourage the free exchange of ideas 
some residents had opposed the memorial because of kerouacs 
heavy drinking and itinerant unconventional lifestyle 
the 100000 memorial is an arrangement of 3by8foot granite 
panels bearing 15 passages from most of kerouacs 20 books and 
essays including the socalled lowell novels doctor sax and 
the town and the city previously the only reference to 
kerouac was his small grave marker on the other side of the city 
i feel very good about this memorial said ginsberg who met 
kerouac when both were students at new yorks columbia university 
in the early 1940s its so that any kid in the next century can 
wander in here and be inspired to language and imagination 
the inscribed panels fit into the park as smoothly as the 
merrimack flows through the city he loved so dearly said stella 
sampas kerouac who married kerouac several years before he died of 
a hemorrhage as a near recluse in st petersburg fla 
the dedication was the first meeting between stella kerouac and 
edith parker his first wife since kerouacs funeral 
to me i see jack as a friend lover and a husband said 
parker 66 of detroit i dont think of him as any different 
friday night parker said she and ginsberg placed a bottle of 
cheap wine on kerouacs grave 
kerouacs only child janet michelle kerouac daughter of his 
second wife joan haverty also attended the opening 
i have such mixed feelings about him and about the park 
said janet kerouac 36 who met her father only twice i probably 
see jack kerouac different than most 
several dozen people from quebec the native home of kerouacs 
parents spoke in french to priests and friends from kerouacs 
boyhood neighborhood across the merrimack river from the park 
while fans wearing kerouac tshirts and carrying copies of his 
books wandered the memorial 
watching the ceremony from a quiet corner was henri cru one of 
kerouacs best friends and the model for the character remi 
boncoeur in on the road 
when jack and i were sitting around new york talking of going 
to sea we dreamed of a lot of things he said but there was 
nothing like this 
</TEXT>
