<TEXT>
intellectuals and communist officials in the 
baltic republic of lithuania have followed two other republics in 
demanding more autonomy from moscow as this weeks party conference 
approaches the official news agency tass indicated saturday 
the communist head of the republic of latvia meanwhile 
criticized intellectuals who made radical demands for sovereignty 
at a stormy meeting of hundreds of writers artists and scientists 
this month 
